		<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="True" name="Sorcerer" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527345838.4" ts_lastsave="1527358837.08" unique_id="13">
			<rich_text>Gifted or cursed with innate magical abilities, Sorcerers are unstable conduits for these supernatural energies.

A person might have been born with a natural affinity for channeling these energies, or perhaps an accident in a magic ritual left them exposed to powers beyond their understanding. The reason why varies, but how the powers manifest between individuals is more common.

A Sorcerer's magical ability is untamed. One might intend to cast a fireball, only to end up in a hellish inferno or barely producing enough heat to warm up a tent. How much the outcome varies comes down to how much time the Sorcerer has spent on mastering the spell they are attempting to cast, with higher mastery narrowing the potential outcomes down to only a few after sufficient practice.

Sorcerers tend to be personalitites of extremes and rarely come off as a random nobody in a crowd. Their shame for the powers that they cant control might have turned them into reclusive, shy and embarrassed individuals, or their anger at these consuming forces bend them towards a hostile and brash nature, picking fights when they rear their heads, or looking for them if they do not.

Playing a Sorcerer means you want to shape your experience around the wild outcomes of their unstable spellcasting.</rich_text>
		</node>
		<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="True" name="Warlock" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527341758.0" ts_lastsave="1527358867.6" unique_id="2">
			<rich_text>Warlocks come in many forms. They can be individuals hellbent on achieving their ambitions and damn any morals, conventions, laws or other people standing in their way. Or how about a downtrodden farmer, pushed to the limit by their lord and seeking the final chance to get control of their own life. To do this, they have strucken a deal with an extraplanar entity to lend them their power, rising them above their feeble mortal form into something capable of living up to their dreams.

These deals, however, are not as simple as might seem at first. These entities care little for the mortals that subject themselves to their will, and will be expecting their obedience in return. They might crave sacrifices to prove their subjects loyalty, or maybe that they adhere to a strict set of rules, a code. Failing to live up to these expectations will results in backlash in one way or another, like physical deformation, curses placed on the Warlock or thoise close to him. Continued disobedience might result in the Warlock being stripped of all their power, their death at the hand of their Master or maybe they are broken, reduced to a gibbering shell of who they once were.

Character

Playing as</rich_text>
