		<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="True" name="Possessed" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527341762.42" ts_lastsave="1527359019.46" unique_id="3">
			<rich_text>The Possessed is a person who has been inbibed with a demon, fiend or spirit. Be this as a result of a ritual gone wrong, a desperate attempt to contain an evil, a curse or whatever reason the player can come up with.

Possessed are generally frailer or less mentally strong than other people, due to their constant struggle to keep the reins on the being inside them. They make up for this however with the possibility of summoning the strength of the being inside to manifest in the physical realm.

Manifesting this power, however, takes a toll on the host. While smaller, sporadic uses of the entity might blow over with time. Calling on it to perform greater deeds or manifest fully as an avatar however might result in dire backlash, with the possibility of the being breaking free of its chains and maybe killing the host in the progress.

Personality wise the possessed can come in all shapes and forms. They might struggle with their demon or live in fear of their own potential. Some might lead relatively normal lives, believing that they have come to good terms with their otherworldly guest, not knowing that such a thing is not possible, since no being wants to live an eternity entrapped within another body.

The Possessed as a class plays with a beneath-average standard performance spiked with great heights. As the adventure progresses and taller and taller tasks are asked of the party however, the odds of the being breaking loose increases. Whatever party or adventure the Possessed follows along in is sure to be visited by death, bless fate it is not the party that succumbs.</rich_text>
